CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 27, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "The Glamorous Cotillion - Scenes from the third annual debutante Cotillion given by Pittsburgh AKAs included...Center photos show part of the smartly gowned patrons who watched avidly as the beautiful pageant unfolded..."
TitMainTitle: Group of men, and women, including one fourth from left wearing polka dot dress, light colored wrap, and wide heart pendant necklace, seated in rows in Syria Mosque for Alpha Kappa Alpha's 1954 Cotillion
